Vixie Dust Travel
=================

Current direction
-----------------
- Multi-page React + Vite marketing site for a travel advisor brand
- Primary goal: convert visitors into qualified trip inquiries
- Secondary goal: support a curated merch shop tied to the travel brand
- Early CRM prototype stores inquiries locally and supports CSV export during development

Pages in place
--------------
- Home
- About
- Services
- Shop
- Resources
- Inquiry

What is live in code now
------------------------
- Hash-based routing for static-host friendliness
- Brand-forward homepage with clearer business positioning
- Dedicated route structure for future growth
- Inquiry form that captures lead qualification details
- CRM helper in `src/lib/crm.js` with Supabase support and local fallback
- Dev-only CRM preview for validating the intake flow
- Starter Supabase schema in `supabase/schema.sql`
- Admin route with Supabase email/password sign-in for private lead review
- Notification framework scaffold in `src/lib/leadNotifications.js` and `supabase/functions/send-lead-notification/`

Environment setup
-----------------
- Copy `.env.example` to `.env`
- Add `VITE_SUPABASE_URL`
- Add `VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`
- If env vars are missing, the inquiry flow falls back to local browser storage

Recommended next build steps
----------------------------
1. Add email automation
   - Immediate inquiry confirmation
   - Internal notification to the advisor
   - Nurture sequence for undecided leads
   - Post-trip review and referral follow-up

2. Add real merch commerce
   - Recommended platform: Shopify
   - Keep product catalog curated and trip-themed
   - Use bundles tied to Disney trips, cruises, and seasonal travel

3. Expand content and SEO
   - Destination guides
   - Planning checklists
   - FAQ-rich service pages
   - Blog posts targeting family travel search intent

4. Replace placeholder homepage copy with client-approved messaging
   - Hero headline and subhead
   - Welcome/brand story section
   - Signature vacations blurbs
   - About page voice and positioning

5. Add analytics and attribution
   - Inquiry starts
   - Inquiry submits
   - Shop visits
   - Product clicks
   - Email signups

Suggested CRM schema
--------------------
- leads
  - id
  - created_at
  - name
  - email
  - phone
  - trip_type
  - travel_window
  - budget
  - party_size
  - merch_interest
  - notes
  - stage
  - source

- follow_ups
  - id
  - lead_id
  - due_at
  - status
  - note

- merch_interest_events
  - id
  - lead_id
  - collection
  - event_type
  - created_at

Success metrics
---------------
- Inquiry conversion rate
- Qualified lead rate
- Inquiry response time
- Email signup rate
- Repeat booking rate
- Merch attach rate per booked client

Admin workflow
--------------
- Public site visitors can submit inquiries anonymously
- Advisors can sign in through the `/admin` route using Supabase email/password auth
- Authenticated users can read and update lead stages

Supabase admin setup
--------------------
1. Open Supabase `Authentication` -> `Users`
2. Create the advisor user with an email and password
3. Confirm the updated `supabase/schema.sql` has been run so authenticated users can `select` and `update` leads
4. Add `VITE_SUPABASE_URL` and `VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` to Vercel
5. Visit `#/admin` and sign in with the advisor email and password
